    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT - 9600, 9700, 9800
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsection id="s05010t" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5073T" revno="T" date="02/11/1997">
        <title>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT - 9600, 9700, 9800</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>9600</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9700</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9800</truckmodel>
                <ucodegroup/>

                <ucode>05708</ucode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The steering column assembly on the 9600, 9700, and 9800 vehicles (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501001">Figure 1</hotlnk>) consists of three major components. The steering wheel
                    is attached to upper steering column shaft, which passes through the steering column housing. The
                    housing is bolted to a bracket at the lowermost part of the dash panel assembly. The upper steering
                    shaft exits the cab via the steering column bracket bolted to the floor.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0501001" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0501001" filename="../figg05/G0501001.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Steering Wheel Column</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. HORN BUTTON</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. HORN BASE PLATE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. SNAP RING</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. STEERING WHEEL MOUNTING NUT</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. SCREW</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. STEERING WHEEL ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. CANCELLING PIN</callout1>
                        <callout1>8. SLIP RING RETAINER</callout1>
                        <callout1>9. HORN CONTACT BRUSH</callout1>
                        <callout1>10. HORN CABLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>11. STEERING COLUMN BUSHING</callout1>
                        <callout1>12. SPLINED PUSH-ON NUT</callout1>
                        <callout1>13. TURN SIGNAL SWITCH</callout1>
                        <callout1>14. STEERING COLUMN HOUSING</callout1>
                        <callout1>15. STEERING COLUMN HOUSING</callout1>
                        <callout1>16. FLAT WASHER 7/8</callout1>
                        <callout1>17. STEERING COLUMN SHAFT SPRING</callout1>
                        <callout1>18. SNAP RING</callout1>
                        <callout1>19. STEERING COLUMN BRACKET BOOT</callout1>
                        <callout1>20. STEERING COLUMN BUSHING</callout1>
                        <callout1>21. STEERING COLUMN BRACKET</callout1>
                        <callout1>22. STEERING COLUMN BRACKET GASKET</callout1>
                        <callout1>23. SEAL</callout1>
                        <callout1>24. STEERING COLUMN SHAFT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>25. END YOKE PINCH BOLT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>26. FLAT WASHER 5/8</callout1>
                        <callout1>27. COMPRESSION SPRING</callout1>
                        <callout1>28. SNAP RING</callout1>
                        <callout1>29. JOURNAL BUSHING</callout1>
                        <callout1>30. STEERING COLUMN MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                        <callout1>31. HEX NUT</callout1>
                        <callout1>32. SPECIAL WASHER</callout1>
                        <callout1>33. SPRING WASHER</callout1>
                        <callout1>34. TILT STEERING WHEEL COLLAR</callout1>
                        <callout1>35. POSITIONING TILT STEERING WHEEL PIN</callout1>
                        <callout1>36. POSITIONING BRACKET</callout1>
                        <callout1>37. DOWEL PIN</callout1>
                        <callout1>38. TILT STEERING WHEEL CAM</callout1>
                        <callout1>39. ROLL PIN</callout1>
                        <callout1>40. TILT STEERING WHEEL POSITIONING LEVER</callout1>
                        <callout1>41. SPRING WASHER</callout1>
                        <callout1>42. SPECIAL WASHER</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <para>The upper and lower steering column shafts are connected through a universal joint that allows
                    articulation. The lower steering column shaft incorporates a slip shaft design to allow for cab
                    tilt. A second universal joint assembly connects the lower steering shaft to the steering gear. The
                    steering column end yoke is fastened to the steering gear input shaft with a pinch bolt assembly.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
